description:
Final part of the Judge Dredd story 'Firestorm' as Dredd squares off against the space pirates and lays down the law, killing them all single handedly, including leader Lucifer Bloodstone.

Cover: Clint Langley (A.B.C. Warriors)

  • Judge Dredd - Firestorm (part 3 - final part) (Robbie Morrison - Sam Hart)
  • The Red Seas - Old Gods (part 7) (Ian Edginton - Steve Yeowell)
  • A.B.C. Warriors - The Volgan War - Book Three (part 6) (Pat Mills - Clint Langley)
  • Stalag 666 (part 7) (Tony Lee - Jon Davis-Hunt)
  • Lobster Random - The Forget-Me-Knot (part 6) (Simon Spurrier - Carl Critchlow)
name: Prog 1606

description: In Los Angeles. Starscream is building an army of his own, now that Megatron has fallen. While in Qatar, Ironhide has been ambushed by Scorponok. The Decepticon has taken control of Ironhide's mind and making him attak the American Army.
name: Starscream's Militia/Scorpion Sting

description:
1. "Kidnapped!" (Superman and Batman) written by Cary Burkett, penciled by Keith Pollard, inked by Mike DeCarlo, colored by Gene D'Angelo and lettered by John Costanza.
  2. "The Hidden Soul of Harmony" (Green Arrow) written by Joey Cavalieri, penciled by Trevor Von Eeden, inked by Larry Mahlstedt, colored by Tom Ziuko and lettered by Adam Kubert.
  3. "Pirates of the Spaceways!" (Hawkman) written by Bob Rozakis, penciled by Alex Saviuk, inked by Frank Chiaramonte, colored by Jerry Serpe and lettered by Phil Felix.
  4. "When Bancroft Fisher Dies, Everybody Dies!" (Captain Marvel, Captain Marvel Jr. and Mary Marvel) written by E. Nelson Bridwell, penciled by Don Newton, inked by Frank Chiaramonte, colored by Adrienne Roy and lettered by Milt Snapinn.

Notes:

  • Superman and Batman cameo in the Hawkman story.
  • Captain Nazi and Sherlock Holmes cameo flashback in the Captain Marvel story.
  • Captain Marvel Jr. and Kid Eternity find out that they are brothers.
name: Kidnapped! / The Hidden Soul of Harmony / Pirates of the Spaceways! / When Bancroft Fisher Dies, Everybody Dies!

description:
Includes the story "S.O.S. ... from Tomorrow!" / written by Robert Kanigher : reprinted from: Superman's Girlfriend Lois Lane #117

Issue #127 is in "Lois Lane Album"
name: S.O.S. ... from Tomorrow!

description:
by Stephen Nilson, Karl Waller & Rick Bonilla Monsterpocalypse

is based on the action-packed, collectible miniatures game of the same name from Privateer Press. The era of monsters is upon us! Giant dinosaur-like creatures roam the southern hemisphere wrecking absolute destruction upon every city in their path. Now mankind has designed their own giant protectors, but will they be enough to save mankind or is our time on Earth up? Three months have past since Gorghadra destroyed most of Chicago and left humanity's defender, Sky Sentinel, for scrap. Sky Sentinel has been rebuilt but his commander is gone, and the crew is not happy with the replacement - Major Jackson Chase, a pilot with a less than perfect military career. Tensions among the crew members escalate when Sky Sentinel is dispatched with an untested commander to defend New York City from an unearthly monster!
name: B.O.H.I.C.A

description: Open warfare between the Cult of Cthulhu and the followers of Nodens has spilled out onto the streets of Arkham, but as their struggle continues to rage, the Harlot reveals that she has not intention of staying on the sidelines during the Godwar. With the help of Lucifer, the Harlot sets her own plans in motion and welcomes back an old friend! Features two alternate covers, by Mateus Santolouco and Nick Percival.
name: Fall of Cthulhu: Godwar

description: Set sail for DEATH! Well...okay, first, unspeakably mind-bending terror on the cruise ship out of time...and then DEATH! Sorry to give away the surprise ending. Also, a sneak peek at our new companion book, FALL OF CTHULHU: GODWAR by horror scribe Michael Alan Nelson!
name: The Doorman

description: Lilli and Pax escape the dinosaur hoard into an ancient village at the tops of the trees where they find a clue to unlocking the mystery of the little girl and the reptile attacks. Meanwhile, the scattered Predator Defense League looks to find allies in their fight against the Talpid occupation.
name: Communication

description:
Many centuries ago, Gods walked among mortals and they wanted to leave a mark. The Demi-Gods and the Giants, are the divine offspring of the celestial beings. But when the Demi-Gods pushed the mighty Giants into oblivion, they became the lords of the planet. Nevertheless, mere humans were not the appropriate companion for the demi-gods and they built Asgard as a haven for all that was blessed. When the Giants were aware of this, they knew it was the moment for payback and what could be sweeter than use Thor himself as their pawn of revenge.

As Asgard fell, dark creatures began invading the human Empire. Even with the help of Thor, now calling himself the Stormbringer, the Empire was impotent to stop its demise caused by the dark horde led by Master Mayhem. Now, Leviticus Cross stands as the last remaining bastion of the Empire, but a growing fear against superhuman beings is spreading among its inhabitants unaware the maybe these rejects from society are the only hope for mankind.
name: Book 1

description:
Overview

Have humanity at large and the culture of complaint we are currently immersed in got you down? Do the phrases "term of empowerment" and "politically correct" bring bile to your throat? Got buttons? White Like She will push them. What is the recipe for controversy? Take one middle-aged black janitor and expose to dangerous working conditions in a nuclear power facility. Remove brain. Add one Generation X Jewish lesbian teenager. Remove brain. Mix. Sell to adults clad in black with requisite piercings and tattoos.
name: Issue 1

description:
Overview

Ever wonder what it would be like to start all over again with a brand-new life? Then White Like She is for you. Post brain-transplant Luther discovers the "joys" of womanhood as he starts his new life in the body of 19-year-old Louella Schwartz. Can you say "sexual harassment"? Luther can, as Tony and crew arrive on the scene, displaying their particular brand of gender insensitivity. Meanwhile, in the brain-juggling clinic, Dr. Fluke gets his hands wet with some new friends...
name: Gettin To Know You

person_credits.name: Bob Fingerman
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description:
Overview

White Like She goes where few books dare to tread, looking the burning issues of the day right in the eye: racial polarity, sexism, and, of course, equal rights for disembodied brains. Luther, a 50-year-old black janitor in the body of a white teenage Jewish lesbian, has his hands full as he confronts Herschel, his "father," with some potentially disturbing news. Elsewhere, Dr. Fluke is taking care of business at the brain-juggling clinic. It's too bad for him the business is with corporate knee-cappers Gregor and Arnie. Meanwhile, brain-in-a-jar Louella starts feeling body conscious...
name: Issue 3

person_credits.name: Bob Fingerman
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description:
Overview

If you're politically correct, run for cover! In the final issue of White Like She, Louella confronts gender inequality... even if it takes a new life in a man's body to do it! Just as Luther makes peace with his new life in a woman's body -- Louella's body -- Louella's disembodied brain looks at life from the other side of the glass ceiling courtesy of the brain-juggling Dr. Fluke.
name: Issue 4

person_credits.name: Bob Fingerman
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description:
Overview

He's big, he doesn't speak, and up until today there hasn't been any way to stop him. But now The Mask's mountainous arch-enemy has finally been brought in by the cops -- and even a reprobate like Walter is entitled to his day in court! Will Walter get sent up the river? Or will he send a flood of violence through the court system? Will he ever speak? And why didn't the mask work on him? None of these questions and more will be answered in the wildest series yet from Dark Horse.
name: Issue 1

description:
Overview

He's mute, he's monstrous, and he's the hottest, new, up-and-coming candidate for political office! After getting his constitutionally guaranteed day in court, Walter rides a wave of populist sentiment that could take him all the way to the mayor's office! The campaign of terror begins in earnest, and with The Mask's massive malefactor on the ballot, the political landscape might never be the same again!
name: Issue 2

description:
Overview

Walter has some very shady friends in some very low places -- and that's just what you need when you're looking to be the mayor of Edge City! But the man-monster-cum-public servant might not complete the mayoral race before the assassin called Mahlon delivers an explosive surprise! Just what does it take to do in a guy who simply won't die? The mystery and mayhem of the campaign trail intensify.
name: Issue 3

description:
Overview

The long (and bloody) campaign trail is finally over for Walter, mute man-monster. After years of battling The Mask and losing, Walter will get a chance to get even when he wins the mayoral seat of Edge City! All the pieces come together to reveal the mystery man behind the whole Walter for Mayor scheme.
name: Issue 4

description:
by Steve Niles & Zid

From the dark mind of Steve Niles (30 Days of Night) comes a story set in the aftermath of our world's collapse. This chilling vision of the future unveils a world where the police patrol for crimes of the imagination. Religious beliefs, along with any tales of false heroes, idols, or gods, are illegal. Detective Philip Khrome doesn't enforce Imagination, he works Homicide. That's where the action is, and he's seen it all before. But criminals evolve, and the world is forever changing. When a killing spree hits his city sector, Khrome finds himself face-to-face with killers born of grim reality with Old World superstition - and everything is not as it seems!
name: A Phillip Khrome Story

description:
"Metal and Mettle, Part Two": You're not just seeing double, you're seeing quadruple when Sonic and Scourge fight for their lives against the sleek killer robots Metal Sonic and Metal Scourge! Why isn't Scourge's Suppression Squad doing anything to help? And what is the sinister secret Dr. Eggman is using to keep the Dark Egg Legion under his control?

The epic battle from the last issue gets even more intense when Metal Scourge comes into the picture to help finish what Metal Sonic started. It just gets so intense that they need to finish it up fast, or move it away from there area so Freedom HQ won't be destroyed! What will happen, you'll need to read it to find out!
name: Metal & Mettle/ Father and Son

description: Tohru Honda was an orphan, living with her grandfather, when one day fate kicked her out of the house and she was forced to take up residence in a tent in the forest. Little did she know that the land she was staying on belonged to the Sohma family, a clan of beautiful and mysterious people. After stumbling upon the teenage squatter, the Sohmas invite Tohru to stay in their house in exchange for cooking and cleaning. Everything's going well until she discovers the Sohma family's greatest secret: when hugged by members of the opposite sex, they each turn into their Chinese Zodiac animal!
name: Vol. 1

description:
Ever since Tohru Honda discovered the Zodiac secret of the Sohma clan, her eyes have been opened to a world of magic and wonder. But with such a great secret comes great responsibility. When her best friends Hana-chan and Uo-chan come to the Sohma house for a sleepover, Tohru has her work cut out for her keeping the 'Cat' in the bag and the 'Dog' on a leash.

Chapter 7 - 12.
name: Vol. 2

description: It's Valentines Day and you know what that means--lots of chocolates for the cutest boys at school! In this case, it's a pretty close tie between hot-headed Kyo Sohma and Yuki 'prince charming' Sohma. Of course the kind-hearted Tohru, guest of the Sohma family, has chocolates for everyone! But when White Day comes around, what will the Sohma family give back? How about a trip to the family hot springs?! Also, a new member of the Zodiac shows up at school to lay the 'MOO'ves on Kyo.
name: Vol. 3

description: When the infamous Akito makes an in-class appearance at the start of the school year, the Sohma family worries that his arrival will be an uncensored exercise of show-and-tell about Yuki's past. Meanwhile, when Ayame vows to rekindle his brothers' lost friendship, he begins to realize that you can choose your friends but you can't choose your family--especially when they're acting like animals!
name: Vol. 4

description: The Sohma household takes to the lake for a vacation at their summerhouse. However, the peaceful silence is deafening, as Yuki and Kyo are once again not on speaking terms. Will Tohru's klutzy kindness get the dueling duo back to their old cat-and-mouse antics once again?
name: Vol. 5

description:
Delving into the recesses of Kyo's past, we find the Sohma trio returning home on a rainy day. There a mysterious man who has known Kyo for a long time meets them. Trust, loyalty and the bonds of family and friendship are tested, as Tohru must help Kyo deal with the "monsters" that he's been trying to avoid.

Chapter 31 - 35.
name: Vol. 6

description: Tohru and company have been having a lot more fun ever since Kisa came to visit. Now it's time for Tohru to meet another member of the Zodiac--the skillfully sarcastic grade-school student, Hiro! One way or another, this tyke will have to deal with his resentment of Tohru and his affection for Kisa!
name: Vol. 7

description: Summer is on its way, so of course Tohru and friends are excited about the upcoming vacation and field trip. But what's that sound? It's Hatsuharu going beserk in the classroom... again! Black Haru is full of more rage than usual, so what will happen when Yuki intervenes? And then there's Ritsu Sohma, whose mom Tohru met at the hot spring; what's wrong with this kimono-wearing beauty?!
name: Vol. 8

description:
Finally summer has arrived! While Tohru struggles through bipolar days of hope and anxiety, what will happen when Yuki comes face-to-face with the new member of the student council?! And...is Uo-chan crazy in love?! Who's that she's hanging out with?! Plus, Hana-chan's past is finally disclosed in a bonus feature! Come join the party in the 9th volume of the super-popular Fruits Basket!

Chapter 49 - 53.
name: Vol. 9

description: Tohru and the Sohmas are spending time at the Sohma family's summerhouse, but it's not all fun in the sun on this little trip. Akito pays a surprise visit, causing a commotion for the rest of the family at the house. Shigure takes a trip down memory lane with an old friend, remembering the days when Hatori wasn't so aloof. Meanwhile, Tohru starts thinking--what must life be like for the parents and lovers of a cursed member of the Sohma family? Can life with this family truly be happy while bearing such a burden?
name: Vol. 10

description: Still at the Sohma family vacation house, Tohru and the gang are obliged to visit Akito everyday because Akito is at the other vacation house. However, day after day relationships get more complicated and forbidden love blossoms. But most importantly Tohru's resolve is hardened when Akito's true identity is revealed.
name: Vol. 11

description: The gang is back from their summer vacation and as the new school term begins, a new student council has finally been assembled, with two new secretaries: Naohito, who has declared himself Yuki's rival, and Kimi who is known as a devil woman who steals men's hearts. Along with the new school term, it's also time for parent-teacher conferences to begin. At that time Tohru goes to see her grandfather, and he brings up a part of Tohru's past that she had tried to shut away.
name: Vol. 12

description:
The mysterious organization known as Machination has struck! On the outskirts of Missouri, Sunstreaker and his human passanger, have been ruthlessly taken out of the game! As Optimus Prime and the Autobots struggle to muster a response to the tragedy, so the Decepticons, now again completely loyal to Megatron, begin to transform their covert strategies into direct actions as Phase 2 begins.

The shocking events of last issue leave the AUTOBOTS reeling. Their number diminished by one, they struggle to come to terms with the whys and wherefores of the Lebanon interception. Similarly, the two humans still standing want answers... and action! And, as if this wasn't enough to contend with, the true, staggering scope of the DECEPTICON Infiltration gambit is revealed!
name: Issue 2

description: When a group of teenagers convinced that they are the 'chosen ones' brings sin rather than salvation, it's up to Subaru and Hokuto to deliver everyone from evil. However, things go from bad to worse when Sieshiro-san takes matters into his own hands while Subaru attempts an exorcism on a member of the chosen ones.
name: Volume 3

description: Subaru Sumeragi gives peace to the dead, but what can he do for the living? When he encounters a woman who is trying to cast a spell to avenge her murdered baby, he tries to stop her... but what will he do when the baby's soul is crying out for revenge?
name: Volume 4

description: What does it take for a girl to stand up for herself? School can be a brutal place, something Kuniko knows firsthand. Classmates beat her, and her teachers can't seem to protect her. When Subaru offers his help, Kuniko finally finds a friendly face. But lurking in the shadows is a deadly force the will stop at nothing to tear them apart.
name: Volume 5

description: Subaru is visibly upset about Seishirou getting his right eye torn out while protecting him. The experience has penetrated Subaru's dreams, where he teaches a lesson to a bunch of punks. Will the visions allow Subaru to see the true meaning of life?
name: Volume 6

description: As the Autobots begin to probe the mysterious abduction (and fate) of Sunstreaker and Hunter O'Nion, Megatron gets hands-on with the escalating Decepticon infiltration strategy on Earth. Having upgraded to an immensely powerful new Earth form, Megatron sets his sights on the soviet state of Brasnya and one of the many facsimile integrated to that particular hot spot.
name: Issue 3

description: Finally, Subaru's memory of his first encounter with Seishirou comes to light. At the same time, Subaru recalls a bet he made with Seishiro a long time ago - a bet where life and death continues to hang in the balance. As Subaru is frozen in the shock of his recollection, Hokuto goes off to fight Seishirou. Don't miss the climactic end of this tragic saga.
name: Volume 7

description:
Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: The Days We Lost ( Ushinawareshi hibi)
  • Chapter 2: It is a Promise! (!! Yakusoku da!!)
  • Chapter 3: Garland of Reunion ( Saikai no hanawa)
  • Chapter 4: Defeated ( Haiboku)
  • Chapter 5: Cathedral ( Daiseid)
  • Chapter 6: Awakening ( Kakusei)
name: Volume 1

volume.name: Saint Seiya: The Lost Canvas - Myth of Hades

description:
Overview

Notes in bottles!

Exotic locals!

Buried treasure!

A whole summer's worth of fun packed into 40 pages!

Join Wacky Squirrel and friends on a treasure hunt that takes them from the wilds of Borneo to the bottom of the sea.
name: Summer Fun Special

description:
Overview

The peaceful planet of Trelkas is invited to become part of a distant alliance of worlds. Some of the Trelkin leaders are cautious, but the Consensus -- their version of parliament or senate -- makes the mistake of sending an envoy to the alliance.
name: Issue 1
12 Thrilling Confession Stories

description: This beautifully rendered and touching story will be the first actual graphic novel series from Top Shelf! Owly is a kind, yet lonely, little owl who's always on the lookout for new friends and adventure. The first graphic novel in the series contains two enchanting novellas, "The Way Home" and "The Bittersweet Summer," wherein Owly discovers the meaning of friendship, and that saying goodbye doesn't always mean forever. Relying on a mixture of symbols, icons, and expressions to tell his silent stories, Runton's clean, animated, and heartwarming style makes it a perfect read for anyone who's a fan of Jeff Smith's Bone or Mike Kunkel's Herobear and the Kid. Don't miss the next big thing in comics!
name: Volume 1

volume.name: Owly: The Way Home & The Bittersweet Summer

name: Free Comic Book Day

description:
Overview

The battle grows on the planet Trelkas as the peace-loving natives try to defend themselves against the invading Broodwarriors. Ignored for his own aggressiveness before the war, scientist Tenris now holds the only hope of defense for the dying world.
name: Issue 2

description: Top Shelf is proud to join the 2008 Free Comic Book Day celebration with not one, but four all-ages tales. In this FCBD edition, we'll not only present an all-new Owly adventure by Andy Runton, but also three other all-new, all-ages adventures from Owly's friends: Korgi by Christian Slade, Johnny Boo by James Kochalka, and Yam by Corey Barba! Perfect for everyone in the family... and be sure to keep an eye out for Owly Volumes 4 and 5, Korgi Book 2, and the debut of Johnny Boo and Yam, all in 2008!
name: Free Comic Book Day 2008

description: Alex Robinson, "the master of true-to-life relationship drama" (Library Journal), has created another tour de force. Tricked follows the lives of six people -- a reclusive rock legend, a heartbroken waitress, a counterfeiter, an obsessive crank, a lost daughter, and a frustrated lover -- whose lives are unconnected until an act of violence brings them spiraling in on each other. Combining intriguing characters with a story structure that is both complex and innovative, Tricked is not to be missed.
name: Tricked

description: In the city of Philadelphia there is a tall building at 18th and Market Street, atop of which lives four individuals. They are the official protectors of the city. Their job is to be around when traditional law enforcement fails. But are they really heroes? Meet Philadelphia's contracted super-hero team: Threshold. A quartet more interested in milk and cookies than crime and punishment. A team more concerned with battling indigestion than their arch enemies. Sure, they have super-powers. They can leap tall buildings, fly, and do all the stuff other heroes do. More than human? Probably. Less than heroes? Without a doubt!
name: Less Than Heroes

description: The rules are simple: you're either a fox or a bunny. Foxes oppress and devour, bunnies suffer and die. Everyone knows their place. Everyone's satisfied. So what happens when a secret desire puts you at odds with your society? Starting from a simple premise - and without using a single word - Fox Bunny Funny leads the reader on a zigzag chase in and out of rabbit holes, and through increasingly strange landscapes where funny animals have serious identity problems. The tale swerves from slapstick to horror and back again before landing at the inevitable climax, in which all the old rules are shattered. When you emerge, you'll find yourself gazing at our own fragmenting society with new eyes!
name: Fox Bunny Funny

description: Masakazu Katsura is one of the most admired manga artists in comics today. And Dark Horse and Studio Proteus are bringing his fabulous creation, Shadow Lady, to you at the insanely low cover price of $2.50! In Gray City, a different world exists between night and day. It is in this city of crime and corruption where we find our unlikely heroine. Aimi Komori is a shy girl, but a shy girl with a secret; her magic eyeshadow transforms her into Shadow Lady, an infamous thief who sees Gray City as her own personal playground. Along with her sidekick, De-Mo, Shadow Lady turns the menacing metropolis upside down.
name: Dangerous Love - Part 1

person_credits.name: Masakazu Katsura
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, inker, colorist, cover

name: Celebrity Roast

description: The story of a small girl and her one-day friendship with a strange boy while on vacation with her family in Hawaii. Their lives are forever changed as they explore the island and themselves. Bookended by full-color biographical excerpts from the life of Japanese filmmaker Akira Kurosawa, the central story's themes reflect those of the filmmaker and are told through black and white half-toned, fully-painted art.
name: The Barefoot Serpent

description: Shadow Lady concludes with a stand-alone, super-sized finale! In this special tale, readers are treated to an "alternate" take on the Shadow Lady story, featuring the main characters as younger, cooler, cuter versions of themselves! This full-length story (with no ads!) features eighteen-year-old Aimi Komori, who is smitten with a new transfer student, Bright Honda. Bright is so obsessed with crime and criminals that his classmates think he's crazy. Aimi receives a special treasure: a magic eye-shadow kit! One brush transforms her from shy schoolgirl to sizzling Shadow Lady, ready to help Bright Honda in his war on the town's crime wave. But when the haughty Bright turns down her help, he unleashes the scorn of a Shadow Lady spurned...but she still wants himt to fall for her! Will he love Aimi ...or her shadowy, sexy alter ego? It's a unique "alternate-universe prequel" story which will entice new readers and thrill die-hard fans! Don't miss out!
name: Special

person_credits.name: Masakazu Katsura
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: A factory of self-replicating robots is stripping the jungle of its natural resources, threatening the territory of a colony of nearby monkeys. A series of encounters between the two groups quickly escalates into all-out war!
name: Monkey Vs. Robot

person_credits.name: James Kochalka
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, cover, production

name: Tales of the Great Unspoken

description: In 1984, Soundwave arrived to Earth in order to investigate Bludgeon's secret plans with Ore-13. When he found out Bludgeon's plan to bring Thunderwing back to life, he decided to stop the Pretenders once and for all. But sadly for Soundwave, he will learn that things are easier said than done.

Kup was a mentor for most of the 'Bot's leaders, like Springer, Optimus Prime, Hot Rod, etc. making him a real hero. Even by the Autobots standards he's way on top. But now, he's stranded in a deadly and dangerous planet, haunted by ghosts and zombies. But lithe the Transformers motto, there's more than meets the eye.
What's the horrible truth behind Kup's nightmares? What will an Autobot risk for a mentor and a friend?

Confronted outside the museum by the Gray City police, Shadow Lady must try a new form in order to escape. And escape she does, only to later meet up with the handsome hunk from earlier. But as Aimi is finding out, appearances can be deceiving.
name: Dangerous Love - Part 2

person_credits.name: Masakazu Katsura
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: Shadow Lady finds herself at a loss when she learns that Bright, the man she had fallen in love with, is a police officer. Furthermore, Bright seems to be overly determined to capture Shadow Lady. Even though Aimi had decided that she was going to quit using her magical eye shadow and stop becoming Shadow Lady, can she do so after she finds out the reason for Bright's determination?
name: Dangerous Love - Part 4

person_credits.name: Masakazu Katsura
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: Aimi and her alter ego find themselves in a perpetual state of melancholy. Aimi is unable to sleep, Shadow Lady just has no motivation to steal anything. The cause of this all? The man who saved her the previous night. He is Bright Honda, one of the newest additions to Gray City's police force.
name: Dangerous Love - Part 3

person_credits.name: Masakazu Katsura
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: Aimi is ecstatic after she learns that Bright's obsessive attitude toward Shadow Lady was not because he had any sort of hatred toward her. Further, the only reason that he came to Gray City was to see her pay for her crimes and set her on the path of justice. But her happiness soon fades when she realizes that Bright's affections are for Shadow Lady and not the timid girl behind the magical make-up...
name: Dangerous Love - Part 5

person_credits.name: Masakazu Katsura
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: Once again Aimi finds herself at a loss, unable to cope with the fact that Bright is in love with Shadow Lady and not with her. She decides never to become Shadow Lady (again) until she happens on an article in a magazine about a temple of love and its famous secret that brings couples together. So, she heads for the temple to steal its secret of love.
name: Dangerous Love - Part 6

person_credits.name: Masakazu Katsura
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: Once more Aimi swears that she'll never be Shadow Lady again . . . But that doesn't last for long when Demota suggests to Aimi that maybe she could get up the courage to tell Bright how she feels if she were to put on some makeup normal makeup. So, the call goes out to Inspector Dory that Shadow Lady is going to go five-finger-discount shopping at the department store...
name: Dangerous Love - Part 7

person_credits.name: Masakazu Katsura
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: As Aimi paces around her apartment trying to come up with some way to get Bright to fall in love with her, Demota asks the simple question, "What do you love about Bright?" To that she finds herself at a complete loss for an answer. Before Aimi can think of what to do next, she runs into Bright during her lunch break...
name: Eyes of a Stranger - Part 1

person_credits.name: Masakazu Katsura
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: Mysterious parts of a message are being left in the biggest banks of Gray City. So far the messages read, "Shadow Lady is . . ." Can it be that someone is onto Shadow Lady's secret identity? When Aimi learns about the possible threat to her secret alter ego, Shadow Lady must try to head off this messenger-thief who could ruin her chances of getting together with Bright for good!
name: Eyes of a Stranger - Part 2

person_credits.name: Masakazu Katsura
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: After the shocking discovery that Shadow Lady has a rival (and one who claims to be a better cat burglar than Shadow Lady), Aimi also finds that a girl named Lime has come looking for Bright. Even though Aimi knows that she'll have to compete with Lime for Bright's affections, Aimi can't stop herself from helping the girl out a bit when she sees that Bright is not exactly thrilled to see this old acquaintance.
name: Eyes of a Stranger - Part 3

person_credits.name: Masakazu Katsura
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: Shadow Lady sends a challenge to the person accusing her of being number two to settle who is better between them. Little does Shadow Lady know that her new rival is Aimi's new friend Lime. Calling herself Spark Girl, Lime is out to capture Shadow Lady to free Bright of his obsession over her.
name: Eyes of a Stranger - Part 4

person_credits.name: Masakazu Katsura
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: Shadow Lady's battle with Spark Girl continues. How will Shadow Lady be able to defeat her new opponent when Spark Girl knows how to reverse the magic eye-shadow transformation? And defeat her Shadow Lady must, because if Spark Girl succeeds, Aimi's true identity will be revealed to the crowd of spectators who've gathered to watch the battle between the rival thieves.
name: Eyes of a Stranger - Part 5

person_credits.name: Masakazu Katsura
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: Aimi's mysterious visitors turn out to be police officers from the demon world. They came to the human realm to arrest De-Mo and take him back to be executed because, according to the laws of the demon world, any contact with humans is punishable by death. In order to save De-Mo's life, Aimi agrees to take on a dangerous mission for the demon world...
name: The Awakening - Part 1

person_credits.name: Masakazu Katsura
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: In order to save De-Mo, Aimi agrees to help the Demon World Police recover the Demon Stones that were stolen and released into the human world. What makes the situation extra difficult is that if anyone finds out what they're doing, or any of the secrets of the Demon World, not only will De-Mo's life be forfeit, so will Aimi's...
name: The Awakening - Part 2

person_credits.name: Masakazu Katsura
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

name: Topolino e Pippo in: I predatori del tempio perduto

description: The epic adventure from Ray Harryhausen and Jules Verne continues! The team becomes separated on the bizarre Mysterious Island as they try to determine what it is they are dealing with. After being attacked by numerous fantastical creatures, they realize they must become proactive in their survival, setting the stage for the battle of a lifetime

volume.name: Ray Harryhausen Presents: Back To Mysterious Island

description: In a gritty sci-fi fantasy world where dinosaurs did not become extinct, humanity lives under the constant threat of giant predators. Protege; hunter Lilli Murko faces off against a deadly carnivore while her Donti Squad discovers a strange new reptilian threat to their city.
name: Unnatural Migration

description: In a world where dinosaurs and humans co-exist, a thousand of the agitated giant reptiles stand between Lilli and a little girl in trouble. But to save the child, the warrior must battle much more than just teeth and claws.
name: Outsider

description: Thousands of dinosaurs descend on Monanti and the entire Predator Defense League is called into action. But if the walls break, are the elite warriors enough to protect the city? And who or what is behind the lizard invasion?
name: Sirens Ring

description:
"LIBERTY"
As things on Earth grow dire, we learn the history of Mars and the events that shaped his life. How does a man become king? How does a king become a god? How does a god become human?
name: Liberty

description: The walls of Monanti City are smashed, and the lives of millions are trampled beneath the feet of relentless dinosaurs. The Predator Defense League tries to stem the tide. The King finds his family kidnapped. But is Lilli to blame? When both father and mentor turn their backs on her, the emotional show-down turns deadly.
name: Numbers Game

description: Lilli is outside the city walls, at the mercy of a thousand dinosaurs relentlessly pursuing her and the child. In the aftermath of the attacks, the mysterious Talpid have taken over Monanti City and are enslaving its citizens. It is up to the remnant of the Predator Defense League to fight on, despite the loss of its greatest leaders.
name: Outside Bad, Inside Worse

description:
"ETERNITY"
From the mind of comic book innovator JONATHAN HICKMAN and pen of super-talent and Image debutant RYAN BODENHEIM comes A RED MASS FOR MARS. In a world that has survived every catastrophe imaginable, a new threat from beyond stars looks to be the end of all humanity.
A RED MASS FOR MARS is a story about the death of utopia, the last days of Earth and the one man who could save us all - but won't.
name: Eternity

description: Galvatron is the herald of death and utter destruction. And a group of Autobots sentinels in Cybertron will learn how painful is to cross in his path. What's the real mission of Galvatron in Cybertron? And who is his dark master? More cybertronian mysteries in the Spotlight series.

Discover the origin of the Sentinel Squad! How did they come together and become the elite group of soldiers to pilot the Sentinels that have made their presence known at the Xavier Institute?

A new group of recruits made their way to the Sentinel Squad and things haven't exactly gone too smoothly. Tempers flared, personalities clashed and at least one member of the team, Alexander Lexington, is hiding something from the others, he's a mutant ! Now the team is struggling to make it through their training. It remains to be seen if this newest Sentinel Squad will be able to make the cut !
name: Tin Can Heroes, Part 1: Machine-Manned

description: Can Warrior Nun Areala and the sea witch Black Coretta work together to defeat the cursed sea captain Edward St. Anthony and his demon master Gorugoth?
name: Sea Demons, Part Two; Bedtime Stories

description: Since Spark Girl has no idea that Aimi is Shadow Lady and was setting a trap for the kidnapper, she tries to save her. But the demon-Kein defeats Spark Girl, and she is changed into stone. After Spark Girl gets zapped, Shadow Lady loses her temper and attacks with all of her power for the first time in her life . . . but will it be enough?
name: The Awakening - Part 3

person_credits.name: Masakazu Katsura
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description:
Big mighty robot action! The men and women of Sentinel Squad are given their very first mission, and not all of them are going to get out of it in one piece! The secret origin of the Sentinels continues!

The news Sentinels are piloted by humans and the newest recruits have been put through the wringer. Their first mission was a catastrophe, as a routine assignment to guard a senator went terribly awry when a Hydra assassin revealed himself, along with a surprise secret weapon. After a long battle, the entire surrounding city was devasted, while the fledgling squad was unable to work as a team. One member, Alexander Lexington, a closeted mutant, was able to save the day, but not before raising suspicion about his powers, and not before another memer of the squad paid a permanent price.
name: Tin Can Heroes, Part 2: Growing Pains

description: Having lost her temper at the kidnapper/murderer who's been terrorizing young women in Gray City, Aimi transforms into Shadow Lady in front of him. Shadow Lady battles the criminal, whose power is enhanced by the demon stone in his possession, but Shadow Lady seems to have the upper hand in the matter . . . that is until the demon sealed inside the demon stone escapes!
name: The Awakening - Part 4

person_credits.name: Masakazu Katsura
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description:
Lets do the math. Giant robots plus dinosaurs equals a nonstop action explosion-thon! The new recruits of the Sentinel Squad are sent to the Savage Land on a highly dangerous rescue mission. But when the squad realizes that this mission means certain death, are they willing to go against their orders to escape being digested by a T. Rex?

Recently, the members of the Sentinel Squad were given a new assignement. They were sent in as reinforcements for an operation in the Savage Land. Facing an army of genetically-enhanced telekinetic dinosaurs, a gung-ho sergeant ordered an entire Sentinel brigade into suicidal combat, and the few squad members who survived did so because of Alexander Lexington, who both defied his C.O.'s orders and revealed to his teammates his secret : that he is actually a mutant !

Now, with most of the pilots dead, and the majority of Sentinel units damaged, Lexington has a plan to defeat the dinosaurs, to stop the Savage Land Mutates, who created this lethal dinosaur army, and to rescue some teammates who have been taken captive. Strangely enough, this plan involves infiltrating the Mutate compound without their Sentinels.
name: Tin Can Heroes, Part 3: Savagery

description: Aimi finds herself no match for escaped demon Medu, who has the ability to turn anyone he looks at into stone. Can Shadow Lady defeat him?
name: The Awakening - Part 5

person_credits.name: Masakazu Katsura
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover
